        "reviewThreads": {
          "nodes": [
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5LeiZ6",
                    "body": "IMHO, this can go near `Polynomial.natDegree_add_le`, e.g., under name `Polynomial.natDegree_add_le_of_le`. See `norm_add_le_of_le` for an example of this pattern already in the library.\r\n\r\nSame for most of the lemmas below.",
                    "createdAt": "2023-07-18T06:32:49Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "urkud"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5Lez0W",
                    "body": "Yuri, thank you for the review!\r\n\r\nI moved almost all the lemmas to `Data/Pol/Deg/Defs`.  In the new file, I left only the lemmas of the form `natDegree ↑n ≤ 0`.  Given that the stronger form `natDegree ↑n = 0` is already present, adding these to the \"main\" library seems unwanted clutter.\r\n\r\nLet me know if you want me to move these lemmas also out of the file, and I can do it!",
                    "createdAt": "2023-07-18T07:45:00Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "adomani"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5Leinn",
                    "body": "BTW, do you handle `(2 : R[X])` (a.k.a. `OfNat.ofNat 2 : R[X]`) in your tactic?",
                    "createdAt": "2023-07-18T06:33:57Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "urkud"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5Le2hR",
                    "body": "I think so.  It seems that special support in this case only touches `0, 1`:\r\n```lean\r\nexample [Semiring R] : natDegree (0 : R[X]) ≤ 0 := by\r\n  compute_degree_le\r\n\r\nexample [Semiring R] : degree (1 : R[X]) ≤ 0 := by\r\n  compute_degree_le\r\n\r\nexample [Semiring R] : natDegree (2 : R[X]) ≤ 0 := by\r\n  compute_degree_le\r\n\r\nexample [Semiring R] : degree (OfNat.ofNat 2 : R[X]) ≤ 0 := by\r\n  compute_degree_le\r\n```\r\nall work with the current tactic.\r\n\r\nHowever, your comment highlighted a bug:\r\n```lean\r\nexample [Semiring R] : degree (OfNat.ofNat 0 : R[X]) ≤ 0 := by\r\n  compute_degree_le\r\n\r\nexample [Semiring R] : degree (OfNat.ofNat 1 : R[X]) ≤ 0 := by\r\n  compute_degree_le\r\n/-\r\ntactic 'apply' failed, failed to unify\r\n  degree ↑?n ≤ 0\r\nwith\r\n  degree (OfNat.ofNat 1) ≤ ?b\r\n-/\r\n```\r\nboth fail.  I'll investigate this in the other PR.",
                    "createdAt": "2023-07-18T07:53:49Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "adomani"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5LiQcH",
                    "body": "These `OfNat` instances use `Zero` and `One`, not `Nat.cast`.",
                    "createdAt": "2023-07-18T20:23:43Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "urkud"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5LiSjL",
                    "body": "I think that I fixed this in the main tactic by using `Expr.numeral?` and being more systematic.\n\nI find the new coercion/numeral system somewhat confusing.  Also, I still think that the special support affects `0, 1` in this case, but from `2` onward it *appears* to be uniform.",
                    "createdAt": "2023-07-18T20:34:02Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "adomani"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5LiJtZ",
                    "body": "Here and below (same for `Int`):\r\n```suggestion\r\ntheorem degree_nat_cast_le (n : ℕ) : degree (n : R[X]) ≤ 0 := degree_le_of_natDegree_le (by simp)\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2023-07-18T19:50:12Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "urkud"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
